The Chronicle LONDON-Britain will allow Chinese telecoms giant Huawei [HWT.UL] a limited role in building its 5G networks, the government said yesterday. It said high-risk vendors would be excluded from the sensitive core of networks, and there would a 35% cap on their involvement in the non-sensitive parts. The United States wanted Prime Minister Boris Johnson to ban Huawei completely, arguing that Beijing could use the companyâ€™s equipment to steal Western secrets. Huawei has denied any involvement in espionage.-Reuters.